    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.02428.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date when="1882-03-27" rend="right">March 27 '82</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Al<ptr target="loc.02428_n1"/></salute>
            </opener>
            <p>First—Love to you and all, May, Bertha, Grace, Kittie &amp; Harry—Second,
                sorry to hear your mother has been down sick &amp; hope the Florida jaunt will help
                her, (as it probably will)—</p>
            <p>—Third, it was I no doubt that sold the Cumberland Street Brooklyn house to
                    Wineburgh<ptr target="loc.02428_n2"/>—What is it your friend wants me to
                do?—Send me word when the coast is all clear, &amp; every thing lovely, &amp; I will
                come on to Mott Haven for a week's visit—I am well as usual</p>
            <closer>
                <signed rend="right">Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
                <p>I write this down in the woods in Jersey but go up to Camden <hi rend="underline">to-morrow</hi><ptr target="loc.02428_n3"/>—</p>
            </postscript>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.02428.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
    </text>
